androidx.core.app

Interface ActivityCompat.OnRequestPermissionsResultCallback

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AppCompatActivity, CarDrawerActivity, FragmentActivity
    Enclosing class:
    ActivityCompat

    public static interface ActivityCompat.OnRequestPermissionsResultCallback
    This interface is the contract for receiving the results for permission requests.

    • Method Detail

      • onRequestPermissionsResult

        void onRequestPermissionsResult(int requestCode,
                                @NonNull
                                java.lang.String[] permissions,
                                @NonNull
                                int[] grantResults)
        Callback for the result from requesting permissions. This method is invoked for every call on #requestPermissions(android.app.Activity, String[], int).

        Note: It is possible that the permissions request interaction with the user is interrupted. In this case you will receive empty permissions and results arrays which should be treated as a cancellation.

        Parameters:
        requestCode - The request code passed in #requestPermissions( android.app.Activity, String[], int)
        permissions - The requested permissions. Never null.
        grantResults - The grant results for the corresponding permissions which is either android.content.pm.PackageManager#PERMISSION_GRANTED or android.content.pm.PackageManager#PERMISSION_DENIED. Never null.
        See Also:
        #requestPermissions(android.app.Activity, String[], int)
